{"TopicId":151983,"ForumId":21,"TopicTitle":"How to make an SSTO that discards its wings?","CreatedByName":"Fireheart318","CreatedById":159932,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-13T17:04:06Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Fireheart318","CreatedById":159932,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-13T17:04:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI want to ditch the wings and jets to improve vacuum efficiency\u00A0but re-dock with them later on for re-entry and landing. Pics and videos are greatly appreciated. Thanks in advance!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-11-13T17:27:27Z\u0022 title=\u002211/13/2016 05:27  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 13, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Fireheart318\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TheDestroyer111","CreatedById":160216,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-13T17:18:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust attach the wings on a decoupler, and use strut connectors in case they bend too much and/or fuel lines if you have fuel inside the wings (the latter\u00A0only applies to Big-S or FAT-455 wings).\u00A0BTW that would remove one of the biggest benefits of \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E spaceplanes over other configurations, which is accurate and controlled landing capability.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Fireheart318","CreatedById":159932,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-13T17:21:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222849155\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151983\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221479057485\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022160216\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022TheDestroyer111\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, TheDestroyer111 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust attach the wings on a decoupler, and use strut connectors in case they bend too much and/or fuel lines if you have fuel inside the wings (the latter\u00A0only applies to Big-S or FAT-455 wings).\u00A0BTW that would remove one of the biggest benefits of \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E spaceplanes over other configurations, which is accurate and controlled landing capability.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv title=\u0022Protected by Grammarly\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI want to re-dock with them later on for landing. I\u0027m planning on taking this particular craft on a trip to Laythe (eventually) but I\u0027m gonna have an Extraplanetary Launchpads base there so I\u0027ll just build the wings there\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TheDestroyer111","CreatedById":160216,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-13T17:25:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222849156\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151983\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221479057703\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022159932\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Fireheart318\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 minutes ago, Fireheart318 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI want to re-dock with them later on for landing. I\u0027m planning on taking this particular craft on a trip to Laythe (eventually) but I\u0027m gonna have an Extraplanetary Launchpads base there so I\u0027ll just build the wings there\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell then, just attach the wings on a docking port that is attached to a docking port... if you need screenshots then HOLD ON\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n//EDIT:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/159932-fireheart318/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022159932\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/159932-fireheart318/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Fireheart318\u003C/a\u003EHere you are:\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022http://imgur.com/a/lmXOR\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://imgur.com/a/lmXOR\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, I know that it\u0027s in KSP 0.25, but it launches 3 times faster than 1.1 (I still couldn\u0027t update to 1.2 due to crappy\u00A0internet provider) and docking ports look and work identically as they do now.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-11-13T17:38:30Z\u0022 title=\u002211/13/2016 05:38  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 13, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by TheDestroyer111\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"royying","CreatedById":20591,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-13T19:26:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow can this kind of craft call \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Fireheart318","CreatedById":159932,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-13T19:29:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222849347\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151983\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221479065196\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002220591\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022royying\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, royying said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow can this kind of craft call \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E: Single Stage To \u003Cb\u003EOrbit\u003C/b\u003E. This would make it into orbit without dropping anything, and then set the wings and jets aside for reentry. Although I agree that it\u0027s kindaaaaa cheating, it\u0027s not really. It abides by the rules and makes more sense than lugging chunks of dry and useless mass around\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-13T19:30:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSingle Stage To Orbit. \u00A0doesn\u0027t say anything about what happens IN orbit\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Starhawk","CreatedById":131400,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-13T19:31:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSince this thread is likely to generate craft designs in response to the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E, it has been moved to the Spacecraft Exchange.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222849347\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151983\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221479065196\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002220591\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022royying\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, royying said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow can this kind of craft call \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s only Single Stage \u003Cstrong\u003Eto\u003C/strong\u003E Orbit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStaging \u003Cstrong\u003Eafter\u003C/strong\u003E you reach orbit doesn\u0027t contradict the definition of \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHappy landings!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Starhawk","CreatedById":131400,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-13T19:34:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSpeaking of example craft...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere\u0027s a spaceplane which delivers a long-range lander to \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Low Kerbin Orbit\u0022\u003ELKO\u003C/abbr\u003E.\u00A0 The lander has a low starting \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E, but over 7 km/s \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Delta-V\u0022\u003EdV\u003C/abbr\u003E.\u00A0 It can land on and return from the Mun, Minmus, Gilly, Ike, Dres, Bop, and Pol.\u00A0 Maybe even Vall.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022s4Meda3.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022750\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/s4Meda3.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHappy landings!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Fireheart318","CreatedById":159932,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-13T19:35:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222849353\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151983\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221479065460\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022131400\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Starhawk\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, Starhawk said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSince this thread is likely to generate craft designs in response to the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E, it has been moved to the Spacecraft Exchange.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s only Single Stage \u003Cstrong\u003Eto\u003C/strong\u003E Orbit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStaging \u003Cstrong\u003Eafter\u003C/strong\u003E you reach orbit doesn\u0027t contradict the definition of \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHappy landings!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv title=\u0022Protected by Grammarly\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI forgot Spacecraft Exchange was a thing. Sorry.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, that\u0027s exactly what I was thinking (SS\u003Cstrong\u003ETO\u003C/strong\u003E)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222849352\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151983\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221479065406\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022linuxgurugamer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, linuxgurugamer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSingle Stage To Orbit. \u00A0doesn\u0027t say anything about what happens IN orbit\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExactly \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DrunkenKerbalnaut","CreatedById":169550,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-13T19:47:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHaving trouble seeing \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/159932-fireheart318/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022159932\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/159932-fireheart318/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Fireheart318\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\u0027s image [ EDIT \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/160216-thedestroyer111/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022160216\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/160216-thedestroyer111/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@TheDestroyer111\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\u0027a image, my bad]\u00A0 \u00A0, but if he didn\u0027t cover it: 2 docking ports ensure repeatable alignment, as long as they are attached to identical sub assemblies. Options: use the 1 to 2 node adapter, or you can stack radial decouplers. The downside of radial decouplers is they can\u0027t attach by node in \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003ESPH\u003C/abbr\u003E, so you would have to be crafty, and if I remember correctly, they fixed the part where they could be docked to things, and their doors closed at the same time.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-11-13T19:49:24Z\u0022 title=\u002211/13/2016 07:49  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 13, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by DrunkenKerbalnaut\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Heckspress","CreatedById":8020,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-13T21:55:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHave a full wingspan assembly that docks on the bottom\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HebaruSan","CreatedById":156657,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-13T22:11:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/8020-heckspress/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u00228020\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/8020-heckspress/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Heckspress\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0suggested, I put the wings, intakes, landing gear, and fuel for atmospheric travel on a detachable structure that starts out joined via a triangle of mini docking ports. This was in whatever version was current on\u00A0October 8, 2014; I\u0027d make a few changes nowadays:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00224E15EF4BA4F21930F24D3595F0C6649678663C81\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022562\u0022 src=\u0022http://images.akamai.steamusercontent.com/ugc/536251481627752262/4E15EF4BA4F21930F24D3595F0C6649678663C81/\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"gchristopher","CreatedById":106024,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-14T00:36:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUnder the pre 1.0 aero, did something a little more complicated than this with the Sporklift/Hot Dog Bun launch system, where a rocket lifted the main payload, then a spaceplane launched, split right down the middle, then welded itself to either side of the rocket to deorbit. This was for the\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/62942-an-affordable-space-program-making-the-reusable-spacecraft-pay-off/\u0026amp;page=6#comment-1081660\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EAffordable Space Program: making the reusable spacecraft pay off\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0challenge, which remains the favorite challenge of any I\u0027ve ever seen posted here.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv data-role=\u0022contentPage\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv data-role=\u0022contentPage\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh, imgur albums don\u0027t work anymore!\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022http://imgur.com/a/FKs0w\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EAlbum here.\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0That\u0027s annoying.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe main problem is that docking ports don\u0027t lock and are absurdly weak for purposes like this one, then and now. You pretty much have to use multiple docking ports, or find a strut or reinforcement mod.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nObviously old-aero design won\u0027t work now, but the approach might.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u002259neTBU.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022750\u0022 src=\u0022http://gchristopher.net/kerbal/59neTBU.jpg\u0022 width=\u0022937\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022pM4j03S.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://gchristopher.net/kerbal/pM4j03S.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022XEMy8xA.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://gchristopher.net/kerbal/XEMy8xA.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Stargate525","CreatedById":53585,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-14T05:52:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222849702\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151983\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221479083813\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022106024\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022gchristopher\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, gchristopher said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv data-role=\u0022contentPage\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv data-role=\u0022contentPage\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe main problem is that docking ports don\u0027t lock and are absurdly weak for purposes like this one, then and now. You pretty much have to use multiple docking ports, or find a strut or reinforcement mod.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI haven\u0027t played much with the new version, but wouldn\u0027t you be able to auto-strut across the ports now, thereby locking them down more securely?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AeroGav","CreatedById":152027,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-14T06:16:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u002220160411122406_1_zpsf7hei7si.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022564\u0022 src=\u0022http://i1144.photobucket.com/albums/o492/narostel/20160411122406_1_zpsf7hei7si.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis was a tight squeeze - if you are building this, \u00A0offset the mark 0 tanks outwards a bit. \u00A0And probably find a better place for the solar panels.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"soulreaver1981","CreatedById":38542,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-14T08:50:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\ni built this a few versions back\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthe front part has the rocket parts\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/wDC55WQ.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 alt=\u0022wDC55WQ.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nand the back has the plane engine\u0027s with you can leave in orbit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/aJWdvfj.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 alt=\u0022aJWdvfj.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-14T11:41:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222849138\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151983\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221479056646\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022159932\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Fireheart318\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 hours ago, Fireheart318 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI want to ditch the wings and jets to improve vacuum efficiency\u00A0but re-dock with them later on for re-entry and landing. Pics and videos are greatly appreciated. Thanks in advance!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTry something like this\u00A0Obiwan hyperdrive docking ring thing\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022VcBUmF7.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022562\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/VcBUmF7.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-11-14T11:53:13Z\u0022 title=\u002211/14/2016 11:53  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 14, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by RevanCorana\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Fireheart318","CreatedById":159932,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-14T20:02:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222849907\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151983\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221479104214\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152027\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AeroGav\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 hours ago, AeroGav said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://i1144.photobucket.com/albums/o492/narostel/20160411122406_1_zpsf7hei7si.jpg\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u002220160411122406_1_zpsf7hei7si.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 height=\u0022564\u0022 src=\u0022http://i1144.photobucket.com/albums/o492/narostel/20160411122406_1_zpsf7hei7si.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis was a tight squeeze - if you are building this, \u00A0offset the mark 0 tanks outwards a bit. \u00A0And probably find a better place for the solar panels.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv title=\u0022Protected by Grammarly\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn addition to those recommendations, I\u0027d add a probe core to the main wing assembly(?) so the nav ball remains in the same position when returning to Kerbin\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AeroGav","CreatedById":152027,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-14T20:06:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222850622\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151983\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221479153746\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022159932\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Fireheart318\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Fireheart318 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn addition to those recommendations, I\u0027d add a probe core to the main wing assembly(?) so the nav ball remains in the same position when returning to Kerbin\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s not just the main wing assembly, it\u0027s the entire aircraft really. \u00A0 Only the cockpit, terrier engine, and one fuel tank (into which all remaining rocket fuel is transferred) undocks to explore deeper space. But as the cockpit section lacks \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003Ercs\u003C/abbr\u003E translation it would be much easier to dock with the airframe again, if you have a way to control the airframe and at least have it orientate itself towards you on approach.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kertech","CreatedById":156079,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-15T00:29:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t know if this will still work, but is the most incredible thing I\u0027ve seen in KSP!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/51808-the-changeling/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Zwolff","CreatedById":58616,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-15T00:40:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know this is not what you asked for, but I tend to build \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/124332-pterion-stock-minmusdunalaythe-capable-ssto-flying-wing/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Emy SSTOs\u003C/a\u003E only using wings that hold liquid fuel, and power them in space with NERVAs. The wings wont be just dead weight, as they tend to hold the majority of the fuel, especially if you refuel in space. But of course I also carry along the RAPIERs, control surfaces, and intakes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sdj64","CreatedById":100819,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-15T04:48:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn 1.2 you can use autostruts to keep your wings rigid even if they\u0027re attached by docking ports. \u00A0It\u0027s\u00A0still useful to use two ports to make sure your wings go back on straight. \u00A0I have not designed something like this but if I did I would probably dock the wing\u00A0above the fuselage as a single piece. \u00A0You can then attach the jets and jet fuel under the wings (if you\u0027re not also using the fuel\u00A0for nuclear engines!).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere\u0027s a more recent design that uses two wings, one above and one below. \u00A0It was made for cargo delivery but I\u0027m sure the concept can be modified to have a reusable space vehicle secured in between with docking ports.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/147335-stock-craft-brainlord-aerospace-yb101-%E2%80%9Cssto-flying-wing%E2%80%9D-40-ton-sandwich-lifter/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-11-15T04:49:25Z\u0022 title=\u002211/15/2016 04:49  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 15, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by sdj64\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"foamyesque","CreatedById":2982,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-15T05:30:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI decided to go big:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022E8E4F4E059956F7BD1F8F4C9CAEEF2B93FF9AF50\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://images.akamai.steamusercontent.com/ugc/145633781835473422/E8E4F4E059956F7BD1F8F4C9CAEEF2B93FF9AF50/\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://images.akamai.steamusercontent.com/ugc/145633781835824392/0C4C96FB3C074B5832925A36D2356BF11D732FE3/\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 alt=\u00220C4C96FB3C074B5832925A36D2356BF11D732FE3\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStill working on the \u0022go home\u0022 part, though.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-11-15T08:01:13Z\u0022 title=\u002211/15/2016 08:01  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 15, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by foamyesque\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HebaruSan","CreatedById":156657,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-16T01:01:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222849525\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151983\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221479075069\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022156657\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022HebaruSan\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 11/13/2016 at 4:11 PM, HebaruSan said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d make a few changes nowadays:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere\u0027s an updated version. This time I wanted enough\u00A0\u0394v to do something interesting, so the crew segment has an LV-N and triple the fuel. Of course, that required the lift segment to have more engines, more fuel, etc. I also added\u00A0a probe core\u00A0so it could hold still during reattachment.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wasn\u0027t able to get all 3 docking ports to dock, either at the runway or in space; but thanks to the locked auto-strutting of the landing gear, the craft holds together without even flexing just from the single mini port at the front. I decided to leave the ports on anyway since that feels kind of exploity. Does anyone know whether\u00A0multiple docking ports can still be auto-docked at launch?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022692C734B07E9F1988BAF23A63F767491A1153320\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022551\u0022 src=\u0022http://images.akamai.steamusercontent.com/ugc/154640637437803811/692C734B07E9F1988BAF23A63F767491A1153320/\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}